    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Refers to the style of sculpture named after a mid-7th century statue of the Buddhist goddess of mercy in the Chuguji nunnery. The style is characterized by figures with rounded, pronounced modelling and soft, supple drapery.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
